{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GiQbShiBuVdQXw2mr9K14n","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F3 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC.md §10 (\"Integrated dev script\"):\n6\t\n7\t- `package.json` `dev` script uses `concurrently` to run both `./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse` and `next dev` together, with labels `-n CH,NEXT` and colors `-c cyan,green`.\n8\t- `concurrently` is listed as a `devDependency` (`^9.0.0`).\n9\t- `predev` hook runs `tsx scripts/migrate.ts` before the dev script (already in place from F2).\n10\t- `concurrently` forwards Ctrl+C to both processes.\n11\t- Running `pnpm dev` starts both ClickHouse and Next.js together.\n12\t\n13\t## Dependencies\n14\t\n15\t- **F1** (`features/F1-done.md`): ClickHouse client singleton at `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`.\n16\t- **F2** (`features/F2-done.md`): Migration script at `scripts/migrate.ts` + `scripts/schema.sql`, `predev` hook already wired in `package.json`.\n17\t\n18\tNo source files are imported or extended — this feature only modifies `package.json`.\n19\t\n20\t## Files to create or modify\n21\t\n22\t- MODIFY `package.json` — change `dev` script to use `concurrently`; add `concurrently` to `devDependencies`.\n23\t\n24\t## Implementation order\n25\t\n26\t1. Add `concurrently` (`^9.0.0`) to `devDependencies` in `package.json`.\n27\t2. Change the `dev` script from `\"next dev\"` to `\"concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \\\"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\\\" \\\"next dev\\\"\"`.\n28\t3. Run `pnpm install` to install the new dependency and update the lockfile.\n29\t\n30\t## Sprint contract\n31\t\n32\t- [ ] File check: `package.json` contains `\"concurrently\"` in `devDependencies` with version `^9.0.0`\n33\t- [ ] File check: `package.json` `dev` script value is `concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\" \"next dev\"`\n34\t- [ ] File check: `package.json` `predev` script value is `tsx scripts/migrate.ts` (unchanged from F2)\n35\t- [ ] File check: `pnpm-lock.yaml` contains `concurrently` (dependency installed)\n36\t- [ ] Type check: `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n37\t- [ ] Lint check: `pnpm lint` exits 0\n38\t- [ ] Build check: `pnpm build` exits 0\n39\t\n40\t## Test plan\n41\t\n42\tNo unit tests are warranted for this feature. The change is purely declarative configuration in `package.json` (two JSON field edits + a dependency addition). There is no business logic, no functions, no modules under test. Correctness is fully covered by the file checks and build/lint/type checks in the sprint contract.\n43\t\n44\t- **Integration gap**: verifying that `pnpm dev` actually starts both ClickHouse and Next.js concurrently requires running the dev server and observing process output — this is a manual/e2e verification.\n45\t\n46\t## Risks and open questions\n47\t\n48\tNone. This is a straightforward `package.json` configuration change. The `concurrently` package handles Ctrl+C forwarding by default — no additional configuration is needed.\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"97709ee1-abe6-4dc2-8be0-c409fd737463","uuid":"1669c16f-24ef-49d8-ba9a-5f057edcf77b","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:10:01.238Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F3-plan.md","content":"# F3 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC.md §10 (\"Integrated dev script\"):\n\n- `package.json` `dev` script uses `concurrently` to run both `./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse` and `next dev` together, with labels `-n CH,NEXT` and colors `-c cyan,green`.\n- `concurrently` is listed as a `devDependency` (`^9.0.0`).\n- `predev` hook runs `tsx scripts/migrate.ts` before the dev script (already in place from F2).\n- `concurrently` forwards Ctrl+C to both processes.\n- Running `pnpm dev` starts both ClickHouse and Next.js together.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **F1** (`features/F1-done.md`): ClickHouse client singleton at `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`.\n- **F2** (`features/F2-done.md`): Migration script at `scripts/migrate.ts` + `scripts/schema.sql`, `predev` hook already wired in `package.json`.\n\nNo source files are imported or extended — this feature only modifies `package.json`.\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- MODIFY `package.json` — change `dev` script to use `concurrently`; add `concurrently` to `devDependencies`.\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. Add `concurrently` (`^9.0.0`) to `devDependencies` in `package.json`.\n2. Change the `dev` script from `\"next dev\"` to `\"concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \\\"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\\\" \\\"next dev\\\"\"`.\n3. Run `pnpm install` to install the new dependency and update the lockfile.\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File check: `package.json` contains `\"concurrently\"` in `devDependencies` with version `^9.0.0`\n- [ ] File check: `package.json` `dev` script value is `concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\" \"next dev\"`\n- [ ] File check: `package.json` `predev` script value is `tsx scripts/migrate.ts` (unchanged from F2)\n- [ ] File check: `pnpm-lock.yaml` contains `concurrently` (dependency installed)\n- [ ] Type check: `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Lint check: `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Build check: `pnpm build` exits 0\n\n## Test plan\n\nNo unit tests are warranted for this feature. The change is purely declarative configuration in `package.json` (two JSON field edits + a dependency addition). There is no business logic, no functions, no modules under test. Correctness is fully covered by the file checks and build/lint/type checks in the sprint contract.\n\n- **Integration gap**: verifying that `pnpm dev` actually starts both ClickHouse and Next.js concurrently requires running the dev server and observing process output — this is a manual/e2e verification.\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\nNone. This is a straightforward `package.json` configuration change. The `concurrently` package handles Ctrl+C forwarding by default — no additional configuration is needed.\n","numLines":49,"startLine":1,"totalLines":49}}}
